Brazilian legend, Rivaldo, has predicted some of the English Premier League matches taking place this weekend. Tottenham will host Arsenal on Sunday evening. Manchester United will tackle Manchester City at Old Trafford on Saturday afternoon. Providing his predictions, Rivaldo told Betfair: “On Sunday, Tottenham host their rival and league leaders Arsenal and I am convinced that the Gunners are a better team right now, so I am going for a 1-0 win for the visitors.” On the Man United vs Man City game, Rivaldo added: “Manchester United will host Man City on Saturday looking to maintain their winning streak against a rival that is chasing the leader Arsenal. In my opinion, home advantage and Man Utd’s good form could be pivotal in this match, and that is why I think they can claim a 2-1 win.”